# Walkthrough
Good Luck!

# directory: raccoon_forest
Game begins here. Barry leaves a hint right away — read it.

cat ./Barry_Help.txt
Then explore.

ls
cd ./oswell_spencer_mansion
> Password: `spencer`

---
# directory: oswell_spencer_mansion → mainhall
You're inside. Use `pwd` to get your bearings — the game will ask you to.

man pwd
pwd
ls

You'll see `doubledoors`. Head there first.

cd ./doubledoors

---
# directory: doubledoors
Explore, then head back.

ls
cat ./Barry_Help1.txt
cd ../ → mainhall

---
# directory: mainhall
Back in the mainhall, Barry suggests searching more carefully.

ls -la

Two hidden doors appear: `browndoor` and `bluedoor`. You'll need passwords for both.
Head back to the doubledoors to look for clues.

cd ./doubledoors

---
# directory: doubledoors

ls -la
cat ./.kennethsullivan.txt
You found something useful on Kenneth's body.

cd ../ → mainhall

---
# directory: mainhall

cd ./browndoor
> Password: `LOCKPICK`

---
# directory: browndoor
Search everything in here — including things that look empty at first.

ls
cat ./WomanStatuewithVase.txt
ls -la
cat ./.something_in_statue_vase.txt
The Keeper's Diary reveals the password for the bluedoor.

cd ../ → mainhall

---
# directory: mainhall

cd ./bluedoor
> Password: `itchytasty`

---
# directory: bluedoor
Read all three files in here. One of them is especially important.

ls
cat ./researcherswill.txt
cat ./NEWSPAPER_CLIPPINGS.txt
cat ./security_protocols.txt

The security protocols mention a hidden elevator and a password buried in the
research below. Now search for what's hidden.

ls -la
cd ./.privateelevator
> Password: `executive`

---
# directory: privateelevator → Umbrella_Laboratory

---
# directory: Umbrella_Laboratory
You're underground now. Use `pwd` when prompted, then look around.

pwd
ls

You'll see four directories. Only `Research_Office` is accessible right now.

cd ./Research_Office

---
# directory: Research_Office

ls
ls -la
cat ./.orders.txt
The orders reveal the password for the `Cultivation_Room` — and something much worse about Wesker.

cd ../ → Umbrella_Laboratory

---
# directory: Umbrella_Laboratory

cd ./Cultivation_Room
> Password: `eagle`

---
# directory: Cultivation_Room

A confrontation with Wesker. And something far worse waiting inside one of the tubes.
After the scene plays out, all remaining doors unlock.

cd ../ → Umbrella_Laboratory

# PLEASE BE AWARE
#### The Ending Split
After escaping the Cultivation_Room, you have a choice.

In Umbrella_Laboratory the files `Holding_Cells` and `Emergency_Helipad`
are now unlocked. This is where your ending is decided.

---
#### Path A — Emergency_Helipad (Good or Bad Ending)
---
# directory: Umbrella_Laboratory
cd ./Emergency_Helipad

Enter the password when prompted:
> Password: `rocket_launcher`

There's a 35% chance of the Good Ending and
a 65% chance of the Bad Ending.
Whether you win or lose, Chris is never found.

---
#### Path B — Holding_Cells first (Great Ending)
---
# directory: Umbrella_Laboratory
cd ./Holding_Cells

---
# directory: Holding_Cells
Barry hints that you should search carefully.
!! CAUTION: Cells 1, 2, 3, 4, 5, 6, 8, 9, and 10 are death traps.
Don't enter them without a reason.

cat ./Barry_Help.txt
grep -r "Chris" .
cd ./Cell_7

After finding Chris, head back out and to the helipad.

cd ../ → /Holding_Cells
cd ../ → /Umbrella_Laboratory
cd ./Emergency_Helipad

Enter the password when prompted:
> Password: `rocket_launcher`

With Chris rescued, you now have a 100% chance of the Great Ending.

---
Endings Summary

| Ending | How to Get It |
|---|---|
| Bad Ending | Go straight to Emergency_Helipad — 65% chance of unlucky |
| Good Ending | Go straight to Emergency_Helipad — 35% chance of lucky |
| Great Ending | Find Chris in Cell_7 first, then go to Emergency_Helipad |

